text.section:
The provisions of this section that apply to insurers also apply to:
a corporation that operates a nonprofit health service plan under Title 14, Subtitle 1 of this article;
a dental plan organization, as defined in § 14-401 of this article;
a surplus lines insurer; and
a health maintenance organization.

If a person knows that the action will result in or contribute to an insurer becoming an impaired insurer, the person may not:
conceal property that belongs to the insurer;
transfer or conceal property of the person or property that belongs to the insurer in contemplation of a delinquency proceeding;
conceal, destroy, mutilate, alter, or falsify a document that relates to the property of the insurer;
withhold a document from a receiver, trustee, or other officer of the court entitled to its possession under this subtitle; or
give, obtain, or receive anything of value for acting or forbearing to act in a delinquency proceeding.
